{
  "texts": [
    "Score-MatchingAnother possible interpretation of diffusion models is to understand them by analogy with score-matching methods, which learn the 'score' (the gradient of log probability) with methods such as Langevin dynamics [105].",
    "Note that the score is known for a Gaussian.",
    "Indeed, in the formalism we have used so far,∇ ln N (x; µ, σ 2) = µ -x σ 2(19)Apply the reparameterization trick from 3.1 to the distribution of x t and obtain∇ ln N (x t; √ ᾱt x 0, (1 -ᾱt)I) = √ ᾱt x 0 -x t (1 -ᾱt) = - ϵ √ 1 -ᾱt(20)Learning this score function with mean-squared error leads to the same optimization problem as 15.",
    "Philosophically, this is much the same as models formulated under the VAE interpretation.",
    "Where the schools of thought differ is in the noising process (which in turns leads to a different sampling process)."
  ]
}